{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "rbac-permissions-e2e",
    "name": "RBAC \u2013 Permissions (GET /admin/permissions, GET /admin/permissions/groups)",
    "description": "E2E tests for:\n  GET /api/v1/admin/permissions\n  GET /api/v1/admin/permissions/groups\n\nFolder execution order:\n  1. setup            \u2014 register + Gmail OTP + verify-email + login\n                         (captures perms_access_token \u2014 plain user, no RBAC permissions yet)\n  2. auth-guard       \u2014 401 on both routes with no Authorization header\n  3. rbac-guard       \u2014 403 on both routes with valid JWT but no rbac:read (plain user)\n  4. owner-bootstrap  \u2014 POST /owner/bootstrap promotes the test user to owner\n                         (owner role grants rbac:read; Require middleware reads DB per request \u2014\n                          no re-login needed; the same perms_access_token becomes effective)\n  5. happy-path       \u2014 200 + body shape on both routes\n\nRoutes:\n  GET /api/v1/admin/permissions\n  GET /api/v1/admin/permissions/groups\nGuard order (both routes): JWTAuth \u2192 RBAC.Require(rbac:read) \u2192 handler\nNo rate limiter on admin routes (JWT-gated).\n\nEnvironment variables required:\n  bootstrap_secret   \u2014 must match BOOTSTRAP_SECRET in .env\n  gmail_test_email   \u2014 Gmail address for OTP receipt\n  gmail_access_token \u2014 OAuth2 token for Gmail API reads\n\nNotes on what is NOT covered here (covered by unit tests):\n  - DB/service error \u2192 500              \u2014 handler_test.go\n  - nil result marshals as [] not null  \u2014 handler_test.go\n  - empty result marshals as [] not null \u2014 handler_test.go\n\nRun `make _e2e-db-clean` and `make _e2e-kv-clean` before each suite run.\nRequires TRUSTED_PROXIES=127.0.0.1/32 in .env.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "// Increment the request sequence counter and derive a unique X-Forwarded-For IP",
          "// for every request so admin-route requests never collide on any shared bucket.",
          "// Requires TRUSTED_PROXIES=127.0.0.1/32 in .env.",
          "const n = (pm.collectionVariables.get('_req_seq') | 0) + 1;",
          "pm.collectionVariables.set('_req_seq', n);",
          "const ip = '10.' + ((n>>16)&0xff) + '.' + ((n>>8)&0xff) + '.' + (n&0xff);",
          "pm.collectionVariables.set('_xff', ip);"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "setup",
      "description": "Registers the gmail_test_email user, fetches the OTP via Gmail API, verifies email, and logs in. Captures perms_access_token (plain user \u2014 no RBAC permissions yet). This same token is reused for rbac-guard (\u2192 403) and, after owner-bootstrap promotes the user, for happy-path (\u2192 200). The RBAC middleware reads permissions from DB on each request so no re-login is needed after bootstrap.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST /register \u2192 201 (setup permissions user)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const email = pm.environment.get('gmail_test_email');",
                  "if (!email) {",
                  "    console.error('[ERROR] gmail_test_email not set in environment \u2014 add it to environment.json.');",
                  "}",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('perms_email', email);",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('perms_password', 'P@ssw0rd1!');"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "pm.test('message field present and non-empty', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().message).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty);",
                  "",
                  "const token = pm.variables.get('gmail_access_token');",
                  "if (!token) { console.warn('[WARN] gmail_access_token not set \u2014 skipping Gmail fetch'); return; }",
                  "",
                  "console.log('[INFO] Waiting 8 s for verification email to arrive in Gmail...');",
                  "const start = Date.now();",
                  "while (Date.now() - start < 8000) {}",
                  "console.log('[INFO] Done waiting. Querying Gmail API (async)...');",
                  "",
                  "const query = encodeURIComponent('subject:\"Verify your\" newer_than:1h');",
                  "pm.sendRequest({",
                  "    url: 'https://gmail.googleapis.com/gmail/v1/users/me/messages?q=' + query + '&maxResults=3',",
                  "    method: 'GET',",
                  "    header: { Authorization: 'Bearer ' + token }",
                  "}, (err, res) => {",
                  "    if (err) { console.error('[ERROR] Gmail list failed:', err); return; }",
                  "    if (res.code === 401) { console.error('[ERROR] Gmail token expired \u2014 refresh at https://developers.google.com/oauthplayground'); return; }",
                  "    const msgs = res.json().messages;",
                  "    if (!msgs || !msgs.length) { console.warn('[WARN] No matching email found in Gmail.'); return; }",
                  "    pm.sendRequest({",
                  "        url: 'https://gmail.googleapis.com/gmail/v1/users/me/messages/' + msgs[0].id + '?format=full',",
                  "        method: 'GET',",
                  "        header: { Authorization: 'Bearer ' + token }",
                  "    }, (err2, res2) => {",
                  "        if (err2) { console.error('[ERROR] Gmail fetch failed:', err2); return; }",
                  "        const msg = res2.json();",
                  "        let body = '';",
                  "        const parts = msg.payload && msg.payload.parts;",
                  "        if (parts && parts.length) {",
                  "            const p = parts.find(x => x.mimeType === 'text/plain') || parts.find(x => x.mimeType === 'text/html');",
                  "            if (p && p.body && p.body.data) body = atob(p.body.data.replace(/-/g, '+').replace(/_/g, '/'));",
                  "        } else if (msg.payload && msg.payload.body && msg.payload.body.data) {",
                  "            body = atob(msg.payload.body.data.replace(/-/g, '+').replace(/_/g, '/'));",
                  "        }",
                  "        if (!body) { console.warn('[WARN] Could not decode email body.'); return; }",
                  "        const match = body.match(/(?<!#)\\b(\\d{6})\\b/);",
                  "        if (!match) { console.warn('[WARN] No 6-digit OTP found in email body.'); return; }",
                  "        pm.collectionVariables.set('perms_code', match[1]);",
                  "        console.log('[INFO] OTP stored in collection variable \"perms_code\":', match[1]);",
                  "    });",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              },
              {
                "key": "X-Forwarded-For",
                "value": "{{_xff}}"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\"display_name\": \"PermsUser\", \"email\": \"{{perms_email}}\", \"password\": \"{{perms_password}}\"}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/register",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "register"]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /verify-email \u2192 200 (consume OTP)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const code = pm.collectionVariables.get('perms_code');",
                  "if (!code) {",
                  "    console.error('[ERROR] collection variable \"perms_code\" is empty \u2014 Gmail fetch did not complete.');",
                  "    console.error('        Check: gmail_access_token is set and not expired, --delay-request >= 8000.');",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('message includes \"verified\"', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().message).to.include('verified'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              },
              {
                "key": "X-Forwarded-For",
                "value": "{{_xff}}"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\"email\": \"{{perms_email}}\", \"code\": \"{{perms_code}}\"}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/verify-email",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "verify-email"]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /login \u2192 200 (capture perms_access_token)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('access_token present', () => pm.expect(body.access_token).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty);",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('perms_access_token', body.access_token);",
                  "console.log('[INFO] Captured perms_access_token (plain user \u2014 no RBAC permissions yet).');"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              },
              {
                "key": "X-Forwarded-For",
                "value": "{{_xff}}"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\"identifier\": \"{{perms_email}}\", \"password\": \"{{perms_password}}\"}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/login",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "login"]
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "auth-guard",
      "description": "Verifies that the JWTAuth middleware rejects requests with no Authorization header on both routes before RBAC or handler logic is reached. GET routes carry no body \u2014 no Content-Type needed.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /permissions \u2014 no Authorization \u2192 401",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "// JWTAuth fires first \u2014 no token means 401 before RBAC check.",
                  "pm.test('status is 401', () => pm.response.to.have.status(401));",
                  "pm.test('code is missing_token', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().code).to.eql('missing_token'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "X-Forwarded-For",
                "value": "{{_xff}}"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/admin/permissions",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "admin", "permissions"]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /permissions/groups \u2014 no Authorization \u2192 401",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
